---
alwaysApply: true
---

- Never commit directly to main or develop.
- Every feature, fix, or module implementation must live on its own branch.
- Branch naming convention:
    feature/[module-name]          e.g. feature/data-prep
    feature/[module-name]-[detail] e.g. feature/backward-analysis-charts
    fix/[what-was-broken]          e.g. fix/zip-handler-encoding
    docs/[what-was-documented]     e.g. docs/architecture-diagram
- Each branch is owned by the team member responsible for that module.
  Do not push to another member's active branch without their knowledge.
- Before merging to develop:
    - README.md implementation status table must be updated
    - DEVELOPMENT_LOG.md must have an entry for the session
    - pytest must pass with no errors on the changed modules
- main is merge-only from develop after the team verifies the full
  pipeline runs end-to-end.
